Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Offering exceptional foot traffic, 570 George Street ticks all the boxes for a retail site selection, enabling astute retailers to capitalise on one of Sydney’s busiest precincts.

With an expansive glass façade, this brand new retail space offers exceptional street visibility, enabling you to exploit window displays, showcase what’s in store and attract customers inside. This sought-after George Street frontage, offers high exposure to commuter traffic, businesses, residential and tourism pedestrians accessing the city’s Haymarket, Darling Harbour and Hyde Park lifestyle precincts. Night and day, this busy George Street location is the major thoroughfare from the CBD to Haymarket.

Sitting opposite Sydney’s Town Hall and close to QVB, The Galleries Victoria and World Square, 570 George Street has access to a diverse mix of customers.

Bustling by day and vibrant by night, your retail business will be perfectly positioned to take full advantage of commuting and tourism patterns as people walk to and from their destinations.


Key features:
- Prime retail position on George Street
- Location quality and strategically positioned opposite Sydney Town Hall, Town Hall Station and a Light Rail stop
- 24/7 retail location
- Diverse customer demographics
- 500sqm of retail space with expansive high ceilings and flexible floor plates
- Located at the base of a landmark commercial building with an extensive architecturally-designed refurbishment

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: MAKE YOUR MARK ON AN ESTABLISHED & PROMINENT CORNER ADDRESS

Common.Highlight.Common.Text: Steps from QVB and Town Hall Station

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE are pleased to offer a prominent opportunity at the busy CBD intersection of George and Park Street for lease. This tenancy sits in a bustling thoroughfare, close to the Queen Victoria Building, Town Hall Train Station and between the QVB and Town Hall light rail stops. 

Sitting between Westpac Bank and the entry into The Galeries Victoria Shopping Centre (TGV), this tenancy offers two large display windows, generous ceiling heights and blade signage. The Galeries Shopping Centre houses a range of high profile brands such as Carhartt, Crumpler, Diesel, Fitness First, Florsheim Shoes, Gorman, The Grounds of the City, Incu, JB Hi-Fi, Muji, Nudie Jeans, Oscar Wylee, The Athlete's Foot and The Body Shop.

Key features:
- High traffic intersection
- Good frontage with large display windows
- Excellent branding opportunities 
- Only steps away from Queen Victoria Building and Town Hall Station
- Neighbouring tenants include:
   - Woolworths
   - Westpac Bank 
   - The Galeries Victoria

310 George Street is exceptionally positioned on the busy thoroughfare to the Hunter Connection and opposite the billion-dollar Wynyard Place development. Sizes available from 20sqm to 60sqm with approximately 26m of frontage.

Key features include:

- Positioned amongst global brands
- On the doorstep of the new light rail system, also close to heavy rail and bus interchange
- Impressive visibility from the entry of Wynyard Station
- Surrounding retailers include: Lululemon, Nike, The Ivy
Precinct (next door to Jimmy’s Falafel), Wittner, Oscar Wylee, Tommy Bahama, CBA and Priceline Pharmacy.

Common.Highlight.Common.Text: Great Exposure from York & Carrington St

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Carrington Street offers a unique opportunity to become part of what will be one Sydney's largest urban transformations.

Located directly adjacent to Wynyard Park and Wynyard Train Station, Carrington Street presents a rare opportunity to position yourself within one of the most connected business and lifestyle precincts within the core of Sydney's city centre.

Adjoining the 75,000sqm* development of Wynyard Place, now is the time to become part of this upcoming transformation.

- Prime ground floor tenancies ranging from 64sqm* – 331sqm*
- 12.2m* - 14.8m* wide glass frontage facing Carrington Street
- Metres to Wynyard Train Station (Sydney's third busiest railway station) and Wynyard Bus Interchange
- Access to grease & exhaust from select tenancies
- Average 4m* high ceilings 
- Expansive external colonnades for seating
- Adjacent to the new Applejack Hospitality venue – Bopp & Tones (60 Carrington Street)
- Metres from Brookfield’s $2billion / 75,000sqm development – Wynyard Place 

Wynyard Place 

With National Australia Bank and Allianz as the anchor tenants, Wynyard Place will deliver:

- 10 Carrington, a premium grade 59,000sqm 27-level commercial office tower
- Restoration of historic Sydney landmarks; Shell House and 285 George Street
- 6,000sqm of high end retail 
- Revitalisation of Wynyard Lane
- Upgrade to Wynyard Station George Street entrance, with delivery of new grand transit hall and public concourse
- Development of 'Carrington Lane', a new site though link providing pedestrian access between Carrington street and George Street.

http://wynyardplace.com.au/ 

For further details or to arrange an inspection, please call Leif Olson 0409 748 136 or Amy Pfeiffer 0401 198 401. 

*Approx.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: FOUR PRIME CBD RETAIL OPPORTUNITIES, METRES TO WYNYARD TRAIN STATION

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
263 George Street is located in the heart of the Sydney CBD. The building sits on the door step of the new light rail, opposite Australia Square and next to MetCentre Shopping Centre. It benefits from excellent pedestrian traffic driven from accessibility to Circular Quay and Wynyard Station. The link from Barangaroo to the CBD exit is located next door to 263 George Street. 

This is a rare chance to secure prime ground floor retail and/or multi-level retail on George Street and an added bonus of securing the branding rights for the building. 

Key features of this this site include:
- Outstanding CBD presence
- Premium CBD footfall
- High profile location 
- Neighbouring the MetCentre  Shopping Centre 
- In close proximity to Wynyard Station and Barangaroo link 
- Opposite Australia Square 
- Close to transport including bus, ferry, light & heavy rail
- Surrounded by national retailers
- 230sqm – 1,000sqm (could be split or combined)
- Excellent ceiling height 
- Opportunity to brand entire building 
- 7 day retail zone

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: PRIME GEORGE STREET RETAIL IN A BOUTIQUE BUILDING

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
17 Castlereagh Street sits on the corner of Hosking Place and in close proximity to Martin Place. The ground floor tenancy benefits from doors and bifold windows onto Castlereagh Street  and large windows down Hosking Place which provide superior visibility. There are great opportunities for signage with a large sign above the doorway and blade sign which is visible from Martin Place. 

Key features:
- Large windows facing onto Castlereagh Street and Hosking Place 
- Corner location with high visibility 
- Neighbours include luxury brands Fairfax & Roberts and Rolex
- Opposite the head office for Macquarie Bank
- In close proximity to Martin Place, MLC Centre as well as the new Sydney Metro Station ( currently under construction) 
- Short or long term leasing options available

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: RETAIL OPPORTUNITY MOMENTS FROM MARTIN PLACE

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Commanding a prime corner position on one of the most thriving pedestrian intersections in the Sydney CBD, 68 Pitt Street puts you firmly centre stage. This tenancy is a short walk from George Street and is surrounded by hotels including the 5 star Radisson Hotel and also in close proximity to a bustling mix of trendy restaurants. It also sits on the busy Circular Quay to Pitt Street Mall thoroughfare.

With a striking facade and floor to ceiling glazing, 68 Pitt Street allows exceptional exposure for a retail business, in the heart of the Sydney CBD.

Key features:
- Exceptional exposure to three streets; Pitt Street, Hunter Street and O’Connell Street
- Prominent corner presence
- 286sqm of retail space
- Excellent ceiling height of over 6 metres
- Significant 40m of street frontage
- Extremely high foot traffic location
- Close proximity to Australia Square, Wynyard Station and Martin Place
- Close proximity to future Sydney Metro Station (due for completion in 2024)
- Strong national tenants with neighbours such as NAB, Westpac, Officeworks, JB Hi-Fi, Radisson Blu Hotel, NIB Dental, Rockpool Bar & Grill, Mejico, plus many more

RARE LOCATION NEAR NEW METRO STATION.

1 Castlereagh Street offers retailers rare access to a recently refurbished opportunity opposite the new Sydney Metro station (currently under construction). This highly sought after and busy corner site captures a vast amount of foot traffic. It is also in close proximity to the current Martin Place train station.  
This premises offers flexibility to take the ground floor in a number of configurations and also the potential to include level 1.

Key features:
- An exceptional branding opportunity 
- Corner location 
- Flagship retail opportunity available
- High foot traffic location
- Suitable for retail or food & beverage 
- Close proximity to Chifley Plaza, 1 Bligh Street and Martin Place
- Strong national tenants as neighbours such as Rolex, Fairfax & Roberts, CBA, Officeworks, Raddison Blu Hotel, NIB Dental, Rockpool Bar & Grill, Spice Temple, Frankies Pizza, White Rabbit plus many more

4-6 Bligh Street is located in the heart of the CBD’s financial core and is strategically positioned amongst iconic precincts such as Circular Quay, The Lands and Education Buildings, MLC Centre, Wynyard Place and Quay Quarter.

Key features include:
- Popular food and beverage destination
- Flagship opportunity
- Suitable for a variety of uses
- Generous ceiling heights
- Male and female amenities
- Proximity to the new metro rail, light rail and heavy rail stations
- Surrounding retailers include Monopole, Tapavino, Hubert, Chophouse, The Carter, Rockpool, Virgin Active plus many more.
- Immediately available

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: NEWLY REFURBISHED RETAIL IN THE CBD CORE

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
50 Pitt Street is in the heart of the financial precinct among Sydney’s premium office towers, restaurants, hotels and entertainment precinct.

This flagship retail opportunity is occupying the corner of Pitt Street and Bridge Street along with the pedestrianised area of Macquarie Place, delivering an exceptional street presence for retail exposure.

Located at the base of a 15-level commercial tower with brand new finishes and furnished suites.

The future proofed asset will include a reinvigorated retail offering, providing a rare opportunity for retailers to position themselves on an iconic corner block.

Key features:
- Full retail redevelopment
- Retail opportunities ranging from 50sqm to 769sqm with the ability to combine tenancies
- Double height glass running along Pitt Street and Macquarie Place 
- Dynamic retail precinct with multiple concepts and loading dock with goods lift
- DA approved for retail redevelopment

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: FLAGSHIP RETAIL OPPORTUNITY ON ICONIC CORNER BLOCK
